  Scenario: In-query call to VOID procedure does not consume rows
    And there exists a procedure test.doNothing() :: VOID:
      |
    And having executed:
    """
    CREATE (:A {name: 'a'})
    CREATE (:B {name: 'b'})
    CREATE (:C {name: 'c'})
    """
    When executing query:
    """
    MATCH (n)
    CALL test.doNothing()
    RETURN n.name AS `name`
    """
    Then the result should be:
      | name |
      | 'a'  |
      | 'b'  |
      | 'c'  |
    And no side effects

